race.comment: BLAZING GURU (3) last appeared five weeks ago when appearing for the first time for the Ross Lomax stable. Picked up nicely in the run home to finish sixth in the 1700m Cowra Cup on that occasion. Races well with the runs spaced. Drawn to enjoy a soft run and in this easier race she looks the testing material. FLASHY ICON (1) added to his large collection of minor placings when runner-up over the mile at Canberra last start, making good late inroads. Has raced once over today's journey and was successful. Must win another one sooner or later. TOULON FACTOR (4) led and tried hard but found a couple better over 1700m at Walcha recently. Genuine old-timer who will give backers a sight again. HOORINI (9) led and gave nothing else a chance over a staying trip at Dubbo last start. Less effective back to this distance but cannot be ruled out. Last start Taree winner MISS DEFY (7) won't find this any harder and must be respected.
